detaileddescription.para:
Output, only in debug mode both code and value that code yield. For instance: inta=1,b=2;
GYOTO_DEBUG_EXPR(a+b);
 will essentially output, only in debug mode: DEBUG:<functionsignature>:a+b=3

Output both code and value that code yield. For instance: inta=1,b=2;
GYOTO_DEBUG_THIS_EXPR(a+b);
 will essentially output: DEBUG:<functionsignature>:a+b=3

Output, only in debug, name and content of array. For instance: inta[]={1,2,3};
GYOTO_DEBUG_ARRAY(a,3);
 will essentially output, only in debug mode: DEBUG:<functionsignature>:a=[1,2,3]
